'The huge incompatibility between the behavior of men and women' in Israel is central to the breakdown of marriages, said Chevra Letzeirim's founder Mendel Gruber.

Of the 75,000 couples who divorce in Israel each year, '95 percent were unhappy even before the wedding. The gap between their idealized image of each other and the reality was too wide for a lasting connection,' Gruber said. 'Later the physical intimacy also withers.'
